### Test API Call for Patient Past Visit
### Endpoint: GET /ehr/v1/past-visit
### Purpose: Retrieve patient visit history for patient account ID 232

# Basic test call
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8081/ehr/v1/past-visit" \
  -H "patient-account-id: 232" \
  -H "patient-profile-id: 232" \
  -H "tdh-sec-iam-user-identity: {\"doctor_account_id\": 1, \"account_type\": 3, \"email\": \"test@example.com\"}" \
  -v

###

# Alternative: With jq for pretty-printing JSON response
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8081/ehr/v1/past-visit" \
  -H "patient-account-id: 232" \
  -H "patient-profile-id: 232" \
  -H "tdh-sec-iam-user-identity: {\"doctor_account_id\": 1, \"account_type\": 3, \"email\": \"test@example.com\"}" \
  -s | jq .

###

# Test with backoffice account (account_type: 4)
curl -X GET "http://localhost:8081/ehr/v1/past-visit" \
  -H "patient-account-id: 232" \
  -H "patient-profile-id: 232" \
  -H "tdh-sec-iam-user-identity: {\"doctor_account_id\": 1, \"account_type\": 4, \"email\": \"backoffice@example.com\"}" \
  -v
